.TH "bl_enter_powerdown" 9 "bl_enter_powerdown" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bl_enter_powerdown \- Programs CPU to enter the specified state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" bl_enter_powerdown
.BI "(struct cpuidle_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct cpuidle_driver *drv "  ","
.BI "int idx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
cpuidle device
.IP "drv" 12
The target state to be programmed
.IP "idx" 12
state index
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Called from the CPUidle framework to program the device to the
specified target state selected by the governor.
